  "text": "In this paper, we report some alarming security implications of tracking human movement via sound waves. Specifically, we present the first active acoustic side-channel attack 1 that can be used to steal sensitive information such as Android unlock patterns. In our attack, human inaudible acoustic signals are emitted via speakers and the echo is [CITATION_1] This paper initially appeared as [CITATION_2] . Linköping University, Linköping, Sweden recorded via microphones, turning the acoustic system of a smart phone into a sonar system. The echo stream not only gives us information about a victim's finger movement but leaks her secrets too.",
